CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: "The D.I.s and Terri - The fabulous group of club women whose benefit for MENDS, last Sunday, was a terrific success, entertained at dinner Saturday night for Terri Springer (far left), their star model. Snapped in Terri's suite at the Penn-Sheraton are members, far left, standing: Margaret Watson, president; seated: Hilda Logan, new member; Bernice Coleman and Mary Jean Eston, associate members; charter members Juanita Drake and Gloria Grate, on floor; on couch, left to right: Evelyn Christian, new member; Birdie Dunlap, associate member, and Nellye Barron, charter member, who was chairman of the affair."
TitMainTitle: Terri Springer standing on left wearing dark dress, in front of D. I. Club members including Margaret Watson, Hilda Logan, Bernice Coleman, Mary Jean Eaton, Juanita Drake, Gloria Golden Grate, Evelyn Christian, Birdie Dunlap, and Nellye Barron, gathered in suite at the Penn-Sheraton Hotel
